<L>__{interior back room tavern night}
<A>__{dark. marion and billings talk over a bottle.}
<C>__{billings}
<D>__{you expect to hold cornwallis with militia?}
<C>__{marion}
<D>__{i expect to try.}
<C>__{billings}
<D>__{trust you and harry lee. remember that damned overland you two thought up in '62 to hit fort louis?}
<C>__{marion}
<D>__{it worked. how many men can you raise?}
<C>__{billings}
<D>__{not many. dalton, scott, they've got their reasons; rev. oliver, he believes in the cause; some of the young bucks; a few like me with nothing to lose...}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{what about you? you've got a lot to lose.}
<A>__{marion drains his glass and stands up.}
<C>__{marion}
<D>__{you coming, or not?}
<A>__{billings drains his glass. they walk out together.}
